msContents.summary: A fragment of Judeo-Arabic commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on Leviticus (5:15-15:33, and 25).

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 24; written lines: 24; One column of text a page, each having 24 lines. The unpointed Hebrew text is embodied. Catchword on every verso.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Yefet. Com. on Leviticus. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2472.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, folio [156v].
